Recommends: raspberrypi-sys-mods, userconf-pi, raspi-config, network-manager, whois, rpi-usb-gadget
Suggests: openssl
Description: first-boot OS customisation for Raspberry Pi OS
 rpi-preseed applies a single human-friendly TOML configuration file on first
 boot, from booted systemd oneshots, reusing the Raspberry Pi helper scripts
 (imager_custom, userconf, raspi-config nonint) with POSIX-shell fallbacks.
 .
 It supports the full Raspberry Pi Imager option surface plus arbitrary runcmds
 in two phases (pre- and post-network), with idempotent run-once semantics,
 secret/PII redaction, and a diagnostics collector. It is built into the image
 in place of the classic firstrun.sh / userconfig.service flow.
